The two notes describe the same patient case but with some differences in detail and focus. The first note is more comprehensive, providing a detailed narrative of the patient's medical history, examination findings, diagnostic investigations, treatment, and follow-up. It includes specific information about the pathology of the mass, the treatment regimen, and the outcome after two years.

The second note is more concise and structured, focusing on key points such as patient information, chief complaint, history of present illness, menstrual and obstetric history, medical and family history, physical examination, investigations, and plan. It lacks the detailed treatment and follow-up information found in the first note.

Overall, both notes cover the same case but with varying levels of detail and emphasis on different aspects of the patient's medical journey.
